  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Tacugama for Sustainable  Oyster</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The &#x2018;Sustainable Oyster Harvesting with the Women of Sorbengi&#x2019; project in Sierra Leone implemented by Tacuguma Chimpanzee Sanctuary aims to restore habitats (mangroves) while creating income generating alternative livelihoods through women empowerment. The objectives of the project are to build resilience to climate change and develop transferrable methods for planning and to execute and monitor biodiversity conservation and improve the quality and connectivity of native forests and woodlands ecosystems. The Key activities include supporting women with harvesting and processing tools/equipment to enhance productivity; provide additional training to promote a wildlife-based eco-tourism venture.</narrative>
  </description>
